%TUTORIAL-------------------  ENHANCED BROWSE/EDIT  --------------------
%OPTION  ===>_ZCMD
%

+The% Sort+command is  used to sort a  Member List on any%two+columns in
 ascending or desceind order. Valid operands are NAME (the default), VER
 CREATED, SIZE, INIT, MOD, ID, TTR, and A or  D for ascending/descending
 If the display if for  a load module PDS,  valid sort operands are ALIA
 SIZE (very useful), ATTR, SSI, MODE and ENTRY.

 For example, enter "SORT SIZE D ID" to sort the display by SIZE in  des
 order and by ID in  ascending order  (ascending is the  default for  al
 fields).  To return the Member  List to its  original order  (sorted by
 name in ascending order), simply enter "SORT".
)PROC
   &ZUP = DST@ENBE
)END
